The paper discusses interactive image segmentation systems, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on the optimization of human-computer interaction (HCI), which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a method for evaluating usability, which involves conducting user studies, and analyzing user feedback, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the user interface (UI) features of interactive segmentation prototypes, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper proposes an automated evaluation scheme, which involves analyzing user actions, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
